    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Although it's not really clear to me what you're trying to achieve, I spotted an obvious error in your code:\n<code>Field.get()</code> expects the object which contains the field as argument, not some (possible) value of that field. So you should have <code>field.get(object)</code>.</p>\n\n<p>Since you appear to be looking for the field value, you can obtain that as:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Object objectValue = field.get(object);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>No need to instantiate the field type and create some empty/default value; or maybe there's something I missed.</p>\n"
  }, {
