    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I post my solution in Kotlin, but it can work with java objects as well.\nI create a function extension so any object can use this function.</p>\n\n<pre><code>fun Any.iterateOverComponents() {\n\nval fields = this.javaClass.declaredFields\n\nfields.forEachIndexed { i, field -&gt;\n\n    fields[i].isAccessible = true\n    // get value of the fields\n    val value = fields[i].get(this)\n\n    // print result\n    Log.w(\"Msg\", \"Value of Field \"\n            + fields[i].name\n            + \" is \" + value)\n}}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Take a look at this webpage: <a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/field-get-method-in-java-with-examples/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/field-get-method-in-java-with-examples/</a></p>\n"
