    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>While this isn't exactly an answer for accessing values using reflection, there’s always a better and more efficient way - <strong>without reflection</strong>! At <strong>compile time</strong>, we can leverage <strong>annotation processing</strong> libraries, and by using the <a href=\"https://github.com/almogtavor/pojo-analyzer\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>pojo-analyzers</code></a> library we can access the getters and setters of fields without relying on reflection, making it the most performant option.</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>@DetailedPojo\npublic class MyClass {\n    public String myField;\n}\n...\nMyClass c = new MyClass(&quot;bla&quot;);\nDetailedMyClass.map.get(&quot;myField&quot;).getFieldValue(c); // bla\n</code></pre>\n"
